post_text:
School is in session next week! This is what an everyday morning welcome would look like for our Hybrid Students. This video was taken at our Downtown site but the procedure will be the same at all of our sites. Students will be asked a series of COVID-19 related questions along with getting their temperature checked upon entry daily. Students will be expected to remain 6 ft. apart from each other, wear a mask all day, sanitize before each class, and follow all of the existing rules and regulations of MNIC. There are markings on the floor that will keep students 6 ft. away from each other while the teachers spray and wipe down tables and chairs before and after each class. The lunchroom and all of the classrooms are set up so all students are at least 6 ft. away from each other and staff. There are hand sanitizer dispensers placed all around our buildings.
MNIC takes COVID-19 very seriously and we will be enforcing these rules daily. Providing education for our students safely is our number one priority!

post_text:
MNIC Students: With the events of the last few days, we know there is a lot of anger, pain, and fear in our communities. We want you to know that the staff at MNIC are here for you to help in any way we can. All of our MNIC school buildings will be open from 9:00 am to 3:00 pm today and tomorrow.

If you feel you need to get away from where you currently are or need someone to talk to, please stop by one of our buildings or reach out to any of our staff. The MNIC social workers are available on Google Classroom from 12:00 to 2:00 and can also be reached by phone.

Stay safe and don't hesitate to reach out if you need us.

post_text: Here at MNIC High School, we encourage students to obtain and know the importance of a diploma. If you know of any youth between the ages of 14 and 21 that need to complete high school please have them enroll today! To ensure our students are getting all the support they need to be continuously successful during the COVID-19 pandemic, we contact our students daily to encourage them to keep their work performance high. We have staff members at our 4 locations with Chromebooks, hot spots, food, and other resources on weekdays from 8:30-4. You can reach out to us by commenting below, sending a direct message through inbox, or visiting our website at mnic.org. Please share this post with your friends and family!

post_text:
Do you want to be a champion? Do you want to be a Mustang? Do you want your High school diploma? Are you behind on credits, have you dropped out, have kids, need job or job training, or housing? Well, we would love to help you out!

Here at Minnesota Internship Charter School (MNIC), we give you the time and attention you deserve and we help you with your graduation plan. We have the resources you need! Such as:

Chromebooks, to use for your classroom assignments in school and out of school.

Free Drivers Ed classes including behind the wheel.

Free bus card that is yours to use all day and night, including weekends.

Short and long term housing resources.

Clothing and food shelves

Jobs and internships programs (CNA for nursing, Forklift Training & Certification)

Tree Trust Program (Get paid, earn credits, while you work)

If you're 14-20 please register at MNIC.org or send a message TODAY!

post_text:
During this period of distance learning, students have several options in order to be marked present for each school day. They can contact any staff member by phone call, text, or email, or log into their Google Classrooms and comment on, or submit assignments.

Students should check their MNIC email accounts every day for updates and information. Students should log into their Google Classrooms every Monday through Thursday from 10:00 to 1:00 for live instruction.

All MNIC sites are open from 8:30 to 3:00 Monday through Friday for students and families to pick up breakfasts and lunches. Students and families are encouraged to reach out to MNIC staff with any additional needs that may arise during this difficult time.

post_text: We're proud to work with Pillsbury United Communities (PUC) to serve our students, families, and community through this difficult time. PUC is MNIC's charter authorizer.
shared_text:
Pillsbury United Communities
April 10 at 2:21 PM ·

A quick peek at our first all-agency Zoom call, bringing together more than 60 of our dedicated community builders. In less than a month, our food programs have distributed almost 100,000 pounds of food to more than 1000 families—and that’s just one of the ways we’re adapting to meet the needs of community. Find the latest information about our continuing services at https://pillsburyunited.org/covid19/programs/

Don’t forget that all of this work depends on the support of our friends and neighbors. The best way you can support us is with a monthly gift. For just $5 a month, you can purchase nearly $450 worth of food for our food shelves over the next 12 months. If you’re able, sign up for a monthly gift at https://pillsburyunited.org/monthly-giving/

post_text:
MNIC High Schools will Remain Open in the Case of an SPPS Teacher Strike
According to local news media, St. Paul Public Schools (SPPS) teachers are planning to strike starting Tuesday, March 10th, if an agreement with SPPS is not reached by the end of day on Monday, March 9th. In light of the potential SPPS teacher strike, MNIC reminds our students, families, and staff that MNIC is not a part of SPPS and therefore our operations will not be impacted by any teacher strike. Students and staff should report to school as usual on Tuesday, March 10th.

post_text: "We may not control all of the events that happen to us but we have the ability to decide not to be reduced by them". This quote by Maya Angelou describes the daily mindset we encourage our staff and students to have at MNIC. We will continue to explore, we will continue to broaden our horizons and we will continue to have and encourage a growth mindset in all that we do. We are the future, so we must explore all that this world has to offer. ❤

post_text:
MNIC Students Intern at the State Captial.

Our staff work to provide Internships that shall provide students with the skills needed for building strong speakers, activists, and character that serve to produce outstanding citizens in our neighborhoods. We prepare our students to meet the social challenges they will confront after graduation with such activities as Leadership Training and Internships at the Minnesota State Capitol with both Democrat and Republican Lawmakers. During these Internships, students are able to apply concepts learned in our Leadership classes during observation of Lawmakers in committee meetings. Students are able to give their opinions relevant to policies being introduced that will have an impact on their lives. The Leadership class matched with Internships at the State Capitol provides students with leadership opportunities, choice making skills and authentic learning as students apply concepts during their Internships that are captured in their reflective papers, interviews and Ethnography reports.

Want your High school diploma? But life has challenged you. Are you behind on credits, have you dropped out, do you have kids, need job or job training, housing, or is your current school too big and overwhelming? Can you use free iPhone? Well, we would love to help you out!

Here at Minnesota Internship Charter School (MNIC), we give you the time and attention you deserve and we help you with your graduation plan. We have the resources you need! Such as:

Free iPhone program, to use for your classroom assignments, to keep in contact with your family, jobs, and other resources.

Free Drivers Ed classes including behind the wheel.

Free bus card that is yours to use all day and night, including weekends.

Short and long term housing resources.

Clothing, food shelves, daycare.

Jobs and internships programs (CNA for nursing, Forklift Training & Certification,

Tree Trust Program (Get paid, earn credits, while you work)

If your 14 to 20 please register today MNIC.org or send a message TODAY!
